# Glass UI — Project Context

This is a Next.js 16 component library built on top of shadcn/ui.
We are building Apple-inspired glass morphism UI components.

## Stack

- Next.js 16 (App Router), TypeScript, React 19.2
- Tailwind CSS for layout and spacing
- shadcn/ui as the base component layer (lives in components/ui/)
- CSS custom properties for all glass tokens
- Radix UI data-state attributes for enter/exit animations — NO Framer Motion
- Web Animations API for imperative exit animations when needed
- Turbopack is the default bundler — do NOT add --turbopack flags, they are redundant

## Next.js 16 Specifics

- Turbopack is stable and default for both next dev and next build
- middleware.ts has been renamed to proxy.ts — use proxy.ts for any network boundary logic
- Route params and searchParams are now async — always await them
- Caching is opt-in via the "use cache" directive — nothing is implicitly cached
- React Compiler is available and stable but not enabled by default
- Minimum Node.js version is 20.9.0
- React 19.2 View Transitions are available natively — prefer these over JS animation
  libraries for page-level transitions

## Project Structure

- components/ui/ → shadcn base components, DO NOT modify these
- components/glass/ → our animated glass components, built on top of ui/
- registry/ → JSON metadata for each component for the shadcn CLI
- app/api/r/[name]/ → API route that serves registry JSON files to the shadcn CLI

## Naming

- Components are named Glass[ComponentName], e.g. GlassCard, GlassButton
- Registry JSON files are kebab-case, e.g. glass-card.json
